      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELDRITCH (5) drew an outside box and was game in defeat when only 0.8 lengths from the winner Victa Wally in second(30.83) at this track. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. Well-placed to take this out. BLACK CHIP (7) produced a moderate performance last time when fifth at this track over 595m behind Canya Vivi (35.70) in a Grade 5/6. Was in the money prior to that. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. KEELEY ROSE (2) box seated before sticking on well to finish 3 lengths away in third (19.85) at this track in a Grade 5 over 342m. Comes through a solid form race last start. Expected to feature again. VICTORY CLUB (4) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
